SIMPLE: forebode
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forebode
<hw>Fore*bode"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Foreboded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Foreboding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>forebodian</ets>;
<ets>fore</ets> + <ets>bodian</ets> to announce. See <er>Bode</er>
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To foretell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be prescient of (some ill or misfortune); to have
an inward conviction of, as of a calamity which is about to happen; to
augur despondingly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His heart <qex>forebodes</qex> a mystery.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sullen, desponding, and <qex>foreboding</qex> nothing but wars and
desolation, as the certain consequence of C⟦ae⟧sar's death.</q>
<rj><qau>Middleton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have a sort of <qex>foreboding</qex> about him.</q> <rj><qau>H.
James.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To foretell; predict; prognosticate; augur;
presage; portend; betoken.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forebode</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Forebode
<hw>Fore*bode"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To foretell; to presage; to
augur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If I <qex>forebode</qex> aright.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forebode</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Forebode
<hw>Fore*bode"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Prognostication; presage.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forebodement</ent>⟦br⟧
